history.content: There is no precedence. There needs to be space in both for you to be enrolled.  No one is enrolled in one without also being enrolled in the other.  If there are more spaces in the discussion you describe as open (the green dot is just confusing noise from campus that doesn't mean a lot) than there are students waitlisted for the lecture ahead of you that have also chosen the same discussion, you will get moved into the class when the waitlist processes (assuming there are no schedule conflicts with other classes you are already enrolled in).

I was #9 on the CS70 summer waitlist where both lecture and discussion were waitlisted, but I dropped the class and re-added it with an open discussion section, and now I'm #63. Does this mean that I'm already in the discussion, just not the lecture? And is it possible for me to still get into the class? I'm pretty confused about the nuances of class enrollment, any help is appreciated!
history.subject: Does lecture or discussion take precedence?
